events.name: SPC AI Gaming Hackathon Demo Night
events.description: ​Stop by SPC to see the final projects produced during the SPC AI Gaming Hackathon! This event is open to the public. Please register so that we have an accurate headcount as space will be limited.If you're interested in hacking please register here.Agenda:​​Science fair style demos from 4:30-5:30pm​​Finalist demos and prize-giving from 5:30-7pm​We have a special lineup of judges including:​Brina Lee-serial entrepreneur currently founding a social stealth startup. She previously co-founded Hamul, a social gaming platform acquired by Roblox and was Instagram’s first female engineer led engineering teams at Quip.​Max Childis the CEO and co-founder ofVolley, the leading creator of AI-powered voice games for smart TVs and smart home devices. Volley’s titles—includingSong Quiz,Jeopardy!, andWheel of Fortune—have been played in over 30 million homes.​Charles Niuis the co-founder and CEO ofFrisson Labs,where he’s building embodied AI companions that can travel the web with you. He has a decade of experience building virtual companions for AR/VR both on indie titles and at Meta. In his free time Charles also runs a YouTube channel dedicated to his favorite game - Age of Empires.​We'll also have prizes and access to some fun products with our friends atOpenAI(+ more coming!)

events.name: -1 to Roblox with David Baszucki
events.description: ​South Park Commons is delighted to hostDavid Baszuckiof Roblox as part of our -1 to Now series!​​​​​Event Details​​​​​​​4:30pm: Doors Open​​​​5:00-6:00pm: Fireside Chat​David Baszucki​David Baszucki is the founder and CEO of Roblox. His vision is to build a platform that enables shared experiences among billions of users. The company has been widely recognized for its innovation and vision under Baszucki’s leadership.​TIME named Roblox one of the “100 Most Influential Companies,” and it has been recognized by Fast Company for innovation on their “Most Innovative Companies” and “Most Innovative Companies in Gaming” lists. Roblox was also recognized as an innovative workplace on Fast Company’s “Best Workplaces for Innovators” list and for its technical innovations on Fast Company’s “Innovation by Design” list.​Previously, David founded Knowledge Revolution, where he and his brother Greg created “Interactive Physics,” a leader in educational physics and mechanical design simulation software. David graduated from Stanford University as a General Motors Scholar in Electrical Engineering.​📢 -1 to Now is a recurring speaker series at South Park Commons exploring how the world's best builders and thinkers took their ideas from -1 to 0 and beyond. Join us for the inside stories of their experiments, pivots, and breakthroughs on the way to where they are today.​​Registration and approval is required and space is limited, so please RSVP soon.​​Please note doors close promptly at 5:30pm and there will be no late admittance.

events.name: SPC Summer 2025 Demo Faire
events.description: ​Curious what the brilliant minds of SPC are up to?​​​​Join us for a showcase of the latest demos from SPC alumni and members.These are no slideshows—live demos only!​​​Demos will be in person at SPC-SF from 1:30-4:30pm PT. After demos wrap we will host an open house until 6pm PT so you can meet the presenters and mix with SPC members. We hope you'll join us in person!​​​Schedule​​​1:00pm PT - Doors open at SPC-SF​​​1:30pm PT - Demos start​​​4:30pm PT - Demos end, open house starts​​​6:00pm PT - Open house ends​​​About South Park Commons​​​SPC is ahome for the most talented technologistsfiguring out what's next—a community designed to turn the chaos of possibility into the clarity of conviction. Whether you're exploring startup ideas, refining your thinking on a new product, or looking to dive into a new domain, we're here to help you get from -1 to 0.
